[15 November 2024] - Sprint 1 Standup 1

What did you work on since the last standup? 
o	Designed the database schema to store usernames and passwords.
o	Researched best practices for secure authentication.
o	Created a basic registration form interface for the app.

What do you commit to next?
o	Set up Hashed Passwords for security. 
o	Begin developing the login functionality to authenticate users against stored credentials.
o	Implement the backend functionality for registering a new user.

When do you think you'll be done?
o	Registration and secure credential storage implementation should be completed within the next 2-3 days.

Do you have any blockers?
o	Finalizing the choice of encryption library for password hashing.



[16 November 2024] - Sprint 1 Standup 2

What did you work on since the last standup? 
o	Designed the basic structure for the search interface.
o	Connected the interface to the database to enable data retrieval.
o	Tested initial queries to fetch book names and the number of results from the database.

What do you commit to next?
o	Refine the search functionality to handle partial matches and case-insensitive queries.
o	Optimize database queries for faster search results.
o	Add error handling for edge cases, such as no results found.

When do you think you'll be done?
o	The search interface with basic functionality should be completed within the next 2 days.

Do you have any blockers?
o	Need to finalize the database indexing strategy to optimize search performance.



[17 November 2024] - Sprint 1 Standup 3

What did you work on since the last standup? 
o	Connected the librarian interface to the database to fetch book inventory data.
o	Implemented initial queries to retrieve book quantities and statuses (in stock or rented).
o	Added functionality to display who currently has rented books and their due dates.

What do you commit to next?
o	Optimize database queries for faster retrieval of inventory data.
o	Develop sorting and filtering options for the librarian interface (e.g., filter by status or due dates).

When do you think you'll be done?
o	The interface with basic inventory tracking functionality should be completed within 3 days.

Do you have any blockers?
o	Struggling with remote database. Currently it is a local database on local machine.
